  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lifesaving support to fire victims - Bhashantek, Dhaka, Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall aims of this project are to meet the practical needs of the fire affected people (especially women, children, adolescent girls, people with disabilities and the elderly) for thier survival in a dignified and respectful manner. We will do this in three ways. Firstly, through the provision of unconditional multipurpose cash grants that will meet those affected&apos;s diversified and self-identified needs; mainly food and shelter materials for minor repair including plastic sheeting. Secondly, a conditional NFI cash grant support (clothing, crockeries etc.) and finally through the distribution of standard hygiene kits along with relevant health hygiene awareness raising messaging.</narrative>
  </description>
